1
00:00:19,482 --> 00:00:24,506
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language.)

2
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:48,541
Hello.

3
00:00:48,541 --> 00:00:49,375
Checking in.

4
00:00:50,166 --> 00:00:51,041
Yes.

5
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:52,333
Ice.

6
00:01:07,875 --> 00:01:09,250
Wait for me.

7
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,333
So annoying.

8
00:01:13,041 --> 00:01:14,041
What's the room number?

9
00:01:14,708 --> 00:01:15,666
Number 8.

10
00:01:16,916 --> 00:01:17,916
My room is Number 8.

11
00:01:17,916 --> 00:01:19,375
Did you make a reservation?

12
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:21,916
No, I didn't.

13
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:23,500
Aren't we staying together?

14
00:01:23,791 --> 00:01:25,375
Who said we are?

15
00:01:25,666 --> 00:01:26,625
Well...

16
00:01:26,916 --> 00:01:29,041
You're the one
who invited me to Khao Yai.

17
00:01:29,041 --> 00:01:30,625
So we're staying together, right?

18
00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:32,583
I invited you to Khao Yai,

19
00:01:32,583 --> 00:01:33,958
but never said we'd share a room.

20
00:01:35,708 --> 00:01:37,416
But I want to stay with you.

21
00:01:37,916 --> 00:01:38,958
Ma'am.

22
00:01:39,416 --> 00:01:40,625
Would you like to book an extra room?

23
00:01:40,625 --> 00:01:41,500
No need.

24
00:01:41,666 --> 00:01:42,958
Yeah!

25
00:01:43,458 --> 00:01:45,583
Wait for me.

26
00:01:50,583 --> 00:01:52,916
The room is so cute.

27
00:01:58,250 --> 00:01:59,916
The bed is soft too.

28
00:02:09,416 --> 00:02:11,083
Come lie on the bed with me.

29
00:02:11,416 --> 00:02:13,458
You sleep on the bed,
and I'll take the sofa.

30
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:17,750
Why sleep on the sofa
when the bed's this big?

31
00:02:18,083 --> 00:02:19,458
I don't like sharing my bed.

32
00:02:20,416 --> 00:02:22,333
But I'm not just anyone.

33
00:02:22,875 --> 00:02:25,833
I'm... the one who's meant
to be with you.

34
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,291
For the rest of my life.

35
00:02:29,875 --> 00:02:31,416
For the rest of my life.

36
00:02:33,291 --> 00:02:34,208
Ice.

37
00:02:40,916 --> 00:02:42,291
So beautiful.

38
00:02:43,166 --> 00:02:44,000
Not too bad.

39
00:02:47,666 --> 00:02:49,666
I didn't mean the view.

40
00:02:51,041 --> 00:02:52,083
Then what do you mean?

41
00:02:52,916 --> 00:02:54,458
I mean you.

42
00:02:54,666 --> 00:02:56,291
The most beautiful in the world.

43
00:02:57,416 --> 00:02:58,416
Don't say that.

44
00:02:58,416 --> 00:03:00,000
I'm just being honest.

45
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:03,500
Do you say this to everyone?

46
00:03:04,333 --> 00:03:05,583
No.

47
00:03:05,916 --> 00:03:08,625
I only say this to you, just you.

48
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,708
Because I truly love you.

49
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:12,458
Do you know what kind of person I am?

50
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:13,666
I'm not as good as you think.

51
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:16,708
I know.

52
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:20,583
I know sometimes you're arrogant.

53
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:21,625
Stuck‑up.

54
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:22,458
Stubborn.

55
00:03:22,583 --> 00:03:23,958
Sometimes not so nice.

56
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:26,333
So why do you still love me?

57
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:31,375
I love everything about you.

58
00:03:32,166 --> 00:03:33,916
Hey, kid, you don't know anything.

59
00:03:34,125 --> 00:03:34,833
Hey...

60
00:03:35,083 --> 00:03:36,791
I'm 21.

61
00:03:38,458 --> 00:03:42,000
Old enough to have my first partner now.

62
00:03:42,958 --> 00:03:44,041
You're shy, aren't you?

63
00:03:44,041 --> 00:03:45,208
That's nonsense.

64
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:47,500
- I'm not shy.
- What are you talking about?

65
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:48,208
Hot.

66
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:49,375
Not at all.

67
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:51,625
The weather is quite nice.

68
00:03:52,625 --> 00:03:54,208
I'm gonna go take a shower.

69
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:56,791
Can I come with you?

70
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,916
Could you dry my hair?

71
00:04:07,583 --> 00:04:08,708
Dry it yourself.

72
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:11,875
I'm exhausted from driving today.

73
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:14,708
My arms are so sore,
I can't dry my hair myself.

74
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:19,541
Just this once.

75
00:04:19,625 --> 00:04:21,333
Thank you.

76
00:04:34,208 --> 00:04:35,750
Thanks.

77
00:04:36,458 --> 00:04:37,916
You're the kindest.

78
00:04:39,708 --> 00:04:42,708
I'm not kind, just too lazy
to listen to you complain.

79
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:47,083
I know... you're kind
but you like to hide it.

80
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,208
Can I ask you a question?

81
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,916
Ask away.

82
00:05:04,083 --> 00:05:06,708
If I tell you I love you every day,

83
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:08,541
every minute,

84
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,250
every second,

85
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,291
will you get bored of me?

86
00:05:17,041 --> 00:05:18,458
I think... I won't be bored.

87
00:05:19,416 --> 00:05:20,666
I just...

88
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:23,666
Just what?

89
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:27,041
Just don't know how to respond.

90
00:05:35,541 --> 00:05:36,458
Then,

91
00:05:36,458 --> 00:05:39,083
I will wait until you know.

92
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:55,833
Your hair's dry.

93
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:04,500
Not really dry yet.

94
00:06:05,208 --> 00:06:06,416
Heh...

95
00:06:06,708 --> 00:06:07,541
Dry it yourself.

96
00:06:07,541 --> 00:06:08,958
Hmm...

97
00:06:30,458 --> 00:06:31,250
Come here.

98
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:34,583
Don't... it's hot.

99
00:06:36,208 --> 00:06:36,791
Stop...

100
00:06:44,041 --> 00:06:45,000
Don't play around.

101
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,708
Can't I just kiss your cheek?

102
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,344
♪Maybe I'll mess this up♪

103
00:06:49,690 --> 00:06:52,464
♪But when you smile at me♪

104
00:06:54,666 --> 00:06:56,500
What did you order, Ice?
It looks so good.

105
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,000
Pork Chorizo Sausage.

106
00:06:58,083 --> 00:06:58,833
What is this?

107
00:06:58,833 --> 00:06:59,291
Oh...

108
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,333
Uh...

109
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,958
Omelet.

110
00:07:02,791 --> 00:07:03,875
I have no idea what it is.

111
00:07:03,875 --> 00:07:04,375
Inside...

112
00:07:04,375 --> 00:07:06,125
Inside, it might be

113
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:08,250
potato, onion...

114
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:09,583
Something...

115
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,041
Should we eat now?

116
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:12,666
I've been waiting for a while.

117
00:07:16,583 --> 00:07:18,166
Hey... Ice.

118
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:22,625
I never thought I'd see you here.

119
00:07:22,625 --> 00:07:23,750
What are you doing here, Tee?

120
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:24,916
I'm here to relax.

121
00:07:25,125 --> 00:07:26,458
There was so much work before.

122
00:07:26,541 --> 00:07:27,333
What are you doing here?

123
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:28,708
I brought my sister for a vacation.

124
00:07:30,541 --> 00:07:31,791
Khanom?

125
00:07:31,958 --> 00:07:33,208
Hello.

126
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:34,708
We haven't seen each other
for a long time.

127
00:07:34,708 --> 00:07:36,916
It's been so long since I saw you, Tee.

128
00:07:37,416 --> 00:07:38,916
May I sit down?

129
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:40,666
Please.

130
00:07:46,416 --> 00:07:47,208
You...

131
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:48,708
You've changed a lot.

132
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:52,125
For the better or worse?

133
00:07:52,541 --> 00:07:54,541
It must be... for the better, right?

134
00:07:55,708 --> 00:07:56,750
Then thank you.

135
00:07:58,541 --> 00:07:59,583
Anyway...

136
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:01,708
Once we're done eating,
shall we go for a walk?

137
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,375
Sure.

138
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:10,041
Okay.

139
00:08:11,333 --> 00:08:12,250
You can finish eating first.

140
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:13,166
Okay.

141
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:17,041
Uh... Ice.

142
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:20,291
Khanom is really cute.

143
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:24,000
I never knew she'd grown up so much.

144
00:08:24,375 --> 00:08:25,875
Yes... she's grown up.

145
00:08:27,666 --> 00:08:30,833
So, do you have a boyfriend yet?

146
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:32,416
Not yet...

147
00:08:33,916 --> 00:08:36,250
Then... may I flirt with you?

148
00:08:38,416 --> 00:08:39,458
Tee...

149
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:39,916
What...

150
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:40,958
What are you talking about?

151
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:42,208
I'm not joking.

152
00:08:42,208 --> 00:08:43,208
Hey... don't.

153
00:08:43,208 --> 00:08:44,041
I'm serious.

154
00:08:44,041 --> 00:08:45,083
No...

155
00:08:55,416 --> 00:08:56,500
Ice.

156
00:08:57,708 --> 00:08:59,916
Is there something wrong?

157
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:01,500
Nothing.

158
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,083
Yes, there is.

159
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:11,416
I noticed you've been quiet
since the afternoon.

160
00:09:13,791 --> 00:09:15,291
You...

161
00:09:15,375 --> 00:09:17,291
I think Tee is a good guy.

162
00:09:18,166 --> 00:09:19,208
You...

163
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:20,791
What do you mean?

164
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:23,166
He's a decent guy.

165
00:09:23,458 --> 00:09:24,291
Handsome.

166
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:26,791
He's educated
and comes from a good family.

167
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:27,875
He suits you well.

168
00:09:29,416 --> 00:09:31,625
You... do you realize

169
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:33,083
what you're actually saying?

170
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:36,333
I just think you should open your heart
to guys sometimes.

171
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:37,500
It might be better.

172
00:09:37,875 --> 00:09:40,333
Does this mean you don't love me?

173
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,625
It's not like that.

174
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,458
I just think you deserve better.

175
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:46,500
Do you know what you're saying
right now is contradictory?

176
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:48,166
And

177
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:51,083
I don't want anything better.

178
00:09:51,375 --> 00:09:52,333
I only want you.

179
00:09:53,041 --> 00:09:55,333
You... I have nothing to offer.

180
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:57,500
I'm a woman.

181
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,500
I can't give you a family.

182
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,416
Don't you consider

183
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:03,583
what I want?

184
00:10:06,125 --> 00:10:08,083
I don't want anything better.

185
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:10,583
I just want you.

186
00:10:12,291 --> 00:10:13,708
It's not possible.

187
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,208
What's wrong, dear?

188
00:10:48,416 --> 00:10:51,083
I don't know what to do.

189
00:10:51,083 --> 00:10:53,208
She doesn't love me.

190
00:10:53,375 --> 00:10:54,958
Hmm...

191
00:10:55,625 --> 00:10:59,625
Or maybe she loves you too much.

192
00:10:59,833 --> 00:11:02,125
She's afraid of making you

193
00:11:02,125 --> 00:11:04,541
unhappy.

194
00:11:05,916 --> 00:11:08,333
What do you mean?

195
00:11:10,291 --> 00:11:12,583
Sometimes, dear.

196
00:11:12,583 --> 00:11:14,750
True love

197
00:11:16,041 --> 00:11:18,625
isn't about possession...

198
00:11:18,625 --> 00:11:21,041
it's about letting go.

199
00:11:23,958 --> 00:11:26,708
Yet if the one who's let go

200
00:11:28,208 --> 00:11:30,625
chooses to stay,

201
00:11:31,666 --> 00:11:35,791
that's what true love is.

202
00:11:46,041 --> 00:11:47,208
Ice...

203
00:11:47,958 --> 00:11:50,458
I saw Khanom crying outside.

204
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:52,208
Tee...

205
00:11:53,583 --> 00:11:55,666
I know you love Khanom.

206
00:11:56,666 --> 00:11:57,666
How did you know?

207
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:03,750
The way you look at her says it all.

208
00:12:04,083 --> 00:12:06,208
But why do you deny it?

209
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:09,208
Because I can't give her anything.

210
00:12:09,583 --> 00:12:12,541
She deserves someone better.

211
00:12:14,458 --> 00:12:17,541
I think... if Khanom truly loves you,

212
00:12:18,583 --> 00:12:21,166
she won't expect anything from you.

213
00:12:22,375 --> 00:12:23,916
What she wants

214
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:25,791
is just you.

215
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,333
And... I'm sorry.

216
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:33,791
For pretending to flirt with Khanom.

217
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,166
You pretended?

218
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:40,125
I've seen you look at Khanom
like that for a long time.

219
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:43,041
But you've never admitted it.

220
00:12:43,166 --> 00:12:44,208
So this time,

221
00:12:44,208 --> 00:12:46,166
I want you to know that

222
00:12:46,458 --> 00:12:48,125
some relationships...

223
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,666
if neglected for too long,

224
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:52,708
you might lose the one you love.

225
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:57,583
I'm just afraid

226
00:12:57,583 --> 00:12:59,708
that... I'll make her unhappy.

227
00:13:01,458 --> 00:13:03,000
If you don't love her,

228
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,625
she might be unhappy.

229
00:13:05,541 --> 00:13:07,083
But if you love her,

230
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:08,750
trust me,

231
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:11,833
it will be the greatest happiness.

232
00:13:57,416 --> 00:13:59,541
Why are you here, Ice?

233
00:14:00,125 --> 00:14:03,625
Are you here to tell me
to date Tee again?

234
00:14:03,625 --> 00:14:04,458
No...

235
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:06,750
I'm here to say that I'm the fool.

236
00:14:09,416 --> 00:14:11,000
How so?

237
00:14:13,541 --> 00:14:16,375
Foolish to think love is letting go.

238
00:14:17,125 --> 00:14:19,333
But in truth, love is about...

239
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:21,166
the courage to admit,

240
00:14:21,166 --> 00:14:22,625
the courage to stay close.

241
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:46,666
Sorry for making you sad.

242
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:48,916
Sorry for making you cry.

243
00:14:48,916 --> 00:14:52,625
Sorry for always rejecting you.

244
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:55,333
And sorry for

245
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:57,791
not accepting my own feelings.

246
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,750
But now,

247
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:06,708
I admit that I love you.

248
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,708
I love you so much that
I'm afraid of losing you.

249
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:16,291
Do you really love me?

250
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,375
Really...

251
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:22,916
I loved you from the first day
I met you.

252
00:15:23,416 --> 00:15:25,541
I just fear that I'm not good enough.

253
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:31,166
For me,

254
00:15:31,541 --> 00:15:33,541
Ice, you're the best.

255
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,833
You won't reject me again, right?

256
00:16:02,958 --> 00:16:05,666
No... I'll never reject you again.

257
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:09,166
Come back to the room with me.

258
00:16:13,541 --> 00:16:14,708
Let's go.

259
00:16:27,541 --> 00:16:29,536
Feels like a dream come true.

260
00:16:38,970 --> 00:16:43,291
♪You look at me
with starlight in your eyes♪

261
00:16:43,291 --> 00:16:45,000
You're so warm.

262
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:48,608
You're warm too.

263
00:16:51,041 --> 00:16:52,224
And smell good too.

264
00:16:54,234 --> 00:16:58,144
♪I'm trembling hands
and doubts I cannot hide♪

265
00:17:01,135 --> 00:17:07,040
♪A garden full of thorns
without the rose inside♪

266
00:17:08,346 --> 00:17:13,229
♪You say you love the way I turn away♪

267
00:17:15,514 --> 00:17:20,608
♪The silence that I wear like yesterday♪

268
00:17:23,106 --> 00:17:28,449
♪But sweetheart,
I'm a storm you shouldn't chase♪

269
00:17:29,856 --> 00:17:36,698
♪I'll only leave you
drowning in my maze♪

270
00:17:36,698 --> 00:17:41,696
♪So why... why do you stay?♪

271
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:50,736
♪When I keep pushing love away...♪

272
00:17:51,642 --> 00:17:56,553
♪Why... do you believe?♪

273
00:17:58,170 --> 00:18:02,880
♪When I'm the hardest thing to read...♪

274
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:08,162
♪You love me
like I'm worthy of the moon♪

275
00:18:11,546 --> 00:18:17,664
♪Like broken things deserve to bloom♪

276
00:18:18,266 --> 00:18:21,024
♪You see through walls
I've built so high♪

277
00:18:21,088 --> 00:18:23,648
I'm not quite used to this.

278
00:18:24,416 --> 00:18:26,112
I'll make sure you get used to it.

279
00:18:30,944 --> 00:18:32,352
You're the cutest.

280
00:18:36,083 --> 00:18:36,992
It's like a dream.

281
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:39,541
It's reality now.

282
00:18:42,791 --> 00:18:43,666
Room number 8

283
00:18:43,666 --> 00:18:46,584
means the most to me in my whole life.

284
00:18:47,625 --> 00:18:49,208
For me, it's the same.

285
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:51,250
It's the beginning of us.

286
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:53,242
But...

287
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:57,250
Suddenly, I started feeling scared.

288
00:18:58,208 --> 00:18:59,333
Scared of what?

289
00:19:00,416 --> 00:19:02,810
Scared that when we go back,

290
00:19:02,976 --> 00:19:05,625
you'll change your mind
and reject me again.

291
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:07,642
Oh, no way. I won't change my mind.

292
00:19:08,375 --> 00:19:10,958
I'll stay with you
until my hair turns gray.

293
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:14,333
I'll stay with you
until my hair turns gray too.

294
00:19:16,986 --> 00:19:19,008
♪Maybe I'm not enough♪

295
00:19:19,008 --> 00:19:21,001
♪Maybe I'll mess this up♪

296
00:19:21,178 --> 00:19:25,176
♪But when you smile at me, I believe♪

297
00:19:25,722 --> 00:19:28,096
♪Quiet nights, gentle touch♪

298
00:19:28,096 --> 00:19:30,371
♪I was lost, now I'm found♪

299
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:32,166
Love you.

300
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:34,750
Love you too.

301
00:19:36,041 --> 00:19:37,166
Wo Ai Ni.

302
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:39,208
Wo Ai Ni too.

303
00:19:39,791 --> 00:19:41,166
I love you.

304
00:19:41,708 --> 00:19:43,083
I love you too.

305
00:19:43,375 --> 00:19:44,541
Hmm...

306
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:45,833
Saranghae.

307
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,500
That's enough, I can't speak Korean.

308
00:19:58,682 --> 00:20:02,432
♪You say I'm beautiful♪

309
00:20:03,354 --> 00:20:06,676
♪When I feel so small♪

310
00:20:07,616 --> 00:20:10,272
♪You hold me tight♪

311
00:20:11,162 --> 00:20:15,280
♪Make everything alright♪

312
00:20:15,706 --> 00:20:19,696
♪I'm done running away♪

313
00:20:19,727 --> 00:20:23,328
♪I'm done hiding my face♪

314
00:20:23,328 --> 00:20:26,938
♪Cause you see all of me♪

315
00:20:28,250 --> 00:20:33,472
♪And you still stay♪

316
00:20:34,464 --> 00:20:36,608
♪In room eight, we found love♪
